TransTexas sees $ 600 mln pre - tax gain in Q2 . TransTexas Gas Corp said Thursday it will record more than a $ 600 million gain in its second quarter ended July 31 as a result of the sale of its Lobo Trend unit . The company gave no specific earnings estimates . Company officials were not immediately available to comment further . The company said Thursday it lost $ 0 . 20 per share in its first quarter , compared with a profit of $ 0 . 04 per share in the same year - earlier period . 
